To extract the values of the `list` dictionary you can define a `ValueOf` lookup type analogous to `keyof`:

    type ValueOf&lt;T&gt; = T[keyof T];

Using this on the `list` value yields a union of all the functions:

    type Functions = ValueOf&lt;typeof list&gt;;

To finally get the union type of all return types of those functions use the [`ReturnType&lt;T&gt;`][1] utility:


    type FunctionReturnList = ReturnType&lt;Functions&gt;;

    // Creates the following type as a union of all return types:
    type FunctionReturnList = {
        a: string;
        b: string;
    } | {
        c: string;
        d: number;
    }

Have a look at this playground [demo][2] to see it in action.


  [1]: https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/utility-types.html#returntypet
  [2]: https://www.typescriptlang.org/play/index.html#code/MYewdgzgLgBANgS2jAvDA3gKBjAZgVzGCgXAEYAuGACgEMroAnBMAcwBoYAjBqZtgJSoAfDXQxanLjAC+A9tjyFipMACYq1YL34cYAEyph8AWy4BTRkJSjq44J32z5mGQG5MmKAE8ADuZgANVo4fHMAeVwAHgAVUTQYgG0Aa3NvEFwYGIBdDy8-AIAxZRJwCFQgkLDIqJ9-DPgkKGE8uqKS1QAlcyh8RjAAGSaK7t7+mIKo4qJSyBbMIA

